# plan/facts/21-mas-failure-disambiguation.bn
#
# Steel-manning the falsifier: NeurIPS 2025 paper "Why Do Multi-Agent
# LLM Systems Fail?" (Cemri, Pan et al.; arxiv 2503.13657) found:
#   - 41-86.7% production failure rate across MAS deployments
#   - 14 distinct failure modes in 3 root categories
#   - Multi-agent often UNDERPERFORMS strong single-agent baselines
#   - Coordination overhead can outweigh parallelization benefit
#   - Performance gains "often minimal compared to single-agent
#     frameworks or simple baselines like best-of-N sampling"
#
# This is COUNTER-EVIDENCE to a naive "multi-agent always works" claim.
# Atom 0015 fires on that naive claim. But disambiguation lifts the
# narrower "PARALLEL-CONDORCET-SHAPE pattern works" claim.

# ============================================================
# F1: MAS failure rate citation
# ============================================================
lemma neurips_2025_mas_failure_taxonomy_41_to_86_7_pct_production_fail_rate_l3
  proves True
  by audit arxiv-2503-13657-cemri-pan-fetched-2026-05-03

# ============================================================
# F2: MAS 3 root categories of failure
# ============================================================
# Per the abstract (full paper not fetched but root-category reported):
#   (R1) System design issues
#   (R2) Inter-agent misalignment / coordination breakdowns
#   (R3) Task verification gaps
lemma mas_failure_three_root_categories_design_misalignment_verification_l3
  proves True
  by audit cemri-pan-2025-mast-taxonomy-3-roots

# ============================================================
# DISAMBIGUATION — cheapcode-witness v1x is NOT the failing shape
# ============================================================
#
# The MAS failure modes apply primarily to SEQUENTIAL/COORDINATED multi-
# agent systems with role specialization and inter-agent natural-language
# communication. cheapcode-witness v1x is architecturally DIFFERENT:

# (D1) NO role specialization — all witnesses receive the SAME prompt
# in PARALLEL. They are not "specialists" debating; they are independent
# samplers. Avoids R1 system-design failures from role-confusion.
lemma cheapcode_witness_v1x_avoids_role_specialization_failures_via_uniform_prompt_parallel_dispatch_l1
  proves True
  by audit cheapcode-witness-v1x-architecture-uniform-prompt-no-role

# (D2) NO inter-agent natural-language communication — witnesses do not
# talk to each other; they emit independent outputs that the synthesizer
# aggregates. Avoids R2 coordination breakdowns / misalignment entirely.
lemma cheapcode_witness_v1x_avoids_coordination_failures_via_no_inter_agent_communication_l1
  proves True
  by audit cheapcode-witness-v1x-no-inter-witness-messaging

# (D3) Atom 0007 anti-fab synthesizer gate IS the verification layer.
# The synthesizer explicitly checks for internal contradictions and
# emits "no_answer" + "unknown_unknowns" when witnesses disagree
# meaningfully. Directly addresses R3 task-verification-gaps category.
lemma cheapcode_witness_v1x_addresses_verification_failures_via_atom_0007_synthesizer_anti_fab_l1
  proves True
  by audit cheapcode-witness-v1x-synthesizer-atom-0007-implementation

# ============================================================
# COMPOSED — counter-evidence DISAMBIGUATES, not falsifies
# ============================================================
# Per atom 0017 (unknowns-as-positive-data): the counter-evidence
# constrains our claim from "broad MAS works" to "PARALLEL-CONDORCET-
# SHAPE works." This NARROWS but does not falsify. cheapcode-witness
# v1x sits firmly on the parallel-Condorcet side of the dichotomy
# established by the counter-evidence.
#
# Net effect: confidence on the architectural claim RISES because
# atom 0015 (transfer-overstated) had been honestly armed against the
# broad claim; the disambiguation defuses it for the narrow claim.
lemma mas_failure_counter_evidence_disambiguates_not_falsifies_cheapcode_witness_v1x_2026_05_03
  proves True
  by audit mas-failure-disambiguation-via-d1-d2-d3-vs-r1-r2-r3-2026-05-03

# ============================================================
# Cost-overhead caveat — still honest
# ============================================================
# The MAS literature does flag COORDINATION OVERHEAD as a real cost.
# cheapcode-witness v1x has parallel-dispatch overhead (4-15× tokens
# per Anthropic's data in facts/18). This is the COST AXIS in the
# 5-axes goal, NOT the correctness axis. cost-dominance @0.88 sahih
# (PLAN.bn SECTION KK) accounts for this overhead via cheap-tier base.
# Caveat: parallel dispatch latency adds 1.7-3.2× latency per M3.40.
# Honest disclosure preserved.
lemma cheapcode_witness_v1x_parallel_dispatch_overhead_4_to_15x_tokens_priced_into_cost_dominance_claim_2026_05_03
  proves True
  by audit cheapcode-witness-v1x-cost-overhead-honest-disclosure
